segments.text: The history of SOCAR. Azerbaijan's oil was
repeatedly described in the works of
medieval scholars and travelers as a great
source of income.
As Marco Polo wrote in the fourteenth
century, people in this region used oil
for medicinal purposes as well as for
export. Inscriptions on a stone found in a
well in Balakani say it was drilled by
foreman Aliyar Mamed Nuroglu in fifteen
ninety-four.
Eighteen forty-seven, a turning point in
oil production was reached in the
nineteenth century, and in eighteen
forty-seven, the first oil wells were
mechanically drilled at Bibiheybat and at
Balakani. Eighteen fifty-nine, the first
white oil refinery facility was built in
Baku. Eighteen seventy-six, a deep
well pump was applied for the first time,
preceding the USA by fifteen years.
Eighteen seventy-seven, the Nobel brothers
founded an oil production and processing
company in Baku. Assets included oil
fields, refineries, the world's first oil
tanker in the Caspian Sea, barges,
railways, hotels, and more. Eighteen
seventy-eight, the railway connecting the
oil fields with the refineries, financed
by the Nobel Brothers company, completed
in April eighteen seventy-nine. Nineteen
oh seven, Baku's oil industry ranked first
in the world, with a production of eleven
point five million tons per year. The
world's longest main oil pipeline,
Baku-Batumi, was built at that time.
Nineteen thirty, for the first time,
electric logging and measurement of the
degree of inclination in the borehole was
implemented in Baku. Nineteen forty-one,
seventy-one point four percent of total
Soviet oil was produced by Azerbaijan,
twenty-three point five million tons. This
production guaranteed the victory of the
Soviet Union in World War Two and made oil
an extremely important factor in the
national economy. Nineteen forty-nine,
Azerbaijan was also the first offshore oil
producer in the world. On November
seventh, nineteen forty-nine, Azerbaijan
and the Caspian Sea became known to the
whole world with the discovery of the Neft
Dashlari, Oil Rocks, field, forty
kilometers offshore and ninety kilometers
from Baku. Nineteen seventy to nineteen
eighty, the Azeri, Chirag, Kapaz, and
Gunashli fields were discovered in water
eighty to three hundred and fifty meters
deep. Gunashli currently produces more
than sixty percent of SOCAR's oil. The
billionth ton of oil was produced in
Azerbaijan. Nineteen ninety-two, by the
decree of the President, the Oil Company
of State of the Republic of Azerbaijan.
Nineteen ninety-four,
on September twentieth, the joint
development and production sharing
agreement for the Azeri, Chirag, and
Gunashli fields, deepwater, was signed.
This became known as the Contract of the
Century. The agreement, signed by eleven
oil companies from eight countries, was a
sign of wisdom and political courage by
the leader of Azerbaijan, Heydar Aliyev.
Increased confidence encouraged oil
companies to come here, opening doors to
foreign investment. So far, SOCAR have
signed thirty-two production sharing
agreements. Nineteen ninety-six, on June
fourth, BP, Statoil, Lukoil, Elf
Aquitaine, France, now
Total, OIEC, Iran, now Nico, TPAO, and
SOCAR
signed a joint development agreement for
the Shah Deniz condensate field in Baku.
Nineteen ninety-seven, the
Baku-Novorossisk northern export pipeline
was put into operation. Nineteen
ninety-nine, the western Baku-Supsa export
pipeline has been put into operation. Two
thousand one, the anniversary of the
signing of the Contract of the Century,
September twentieth, is now celebrated
annually as Oilman's Day in Azerbaijan.
Two thousand six,
on May twenty-eighth, the first oil
arrived at the port of Ceyhan through the
Baku-Tbilisi-Ceyhan main export pipeline.
On July thirteenth, the official opening
ceremony of the pipeline took place in the
port of Ceyhan.
Two thousand seven, South Caucasus
pipeline, Baku-Tbilisi-Erzurum, was put
into operation, the first gas export from
Azerbaijan. SOCAR opens the first
representative office in Romania. Two
thousand eight, establishment of SOCAR
Trading SA in Switzerland, in Geneva, to
market Azeri light oil and to increase the
general competitiveness on the world
markets. SOCAR trades oil and oil products
with SOCAR Trading, based in Switzerland,
and through its representative offices in
eight countries. After taking a giant
step into Turkey as a sister country and
strategic partner, SOCAR acquired Petkim
and accelerated its operations in the
country. Investments include gigantic
projects such as the ten million ton Star
Refinery, the one point five million TEU
Petlim Container Terminal, one thousand
five hundred megawatt power plants, and
gas storage facilities liquids. Two
thousand nine to two thousand eleven,
SOCAR built a fuel distribution chain of
forty-seven gas and filling stations in
Ukraine, one hundred and twelve in
Georgia, and thirteen Romania, as well as
acquisition of Esso, ExxonMobil, operating
a wide distribution network in
Switzerland. Two thousand seventeen,
Azerbaijan produced two billion tons of
oil. Two thousand eighteen, the Star
Refinery was inaugurated in an
international ceremony. This was achieved
with an investment value of six point
three billion dollars by SOCAR, Turkey's
largest foreign direct investor. TANAP,
the Silk Road for Energy, was opened in a
ceremony held in Eskisehir with the
participation of the presidents of the two
states.
SOCAR Turkey won the tender for nine gas
stations in Istanbul Airport. The Southern
Gas Corridor project is officially opened
in Baku. Two thousand twenty,
the Trans Adriatic Gas Pipeline, TAP, the
last segment of the Southern Gas Corridor,
began transporting commercial gas from
Azerbaijan.
